==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spurred
<hw>Spurred</hw> <pr>(sp⟦ucir⟧rd)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Wearing spurs; furnished with a spur or spurs; having shoots like
spurs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Affected with spur, or ergot; <as>as,
<ex>spurred</ex> rye</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Spurred corolla</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>a
corolla in which there are one or more petals with a spur.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spurrer</ent>⟦br⟧
